title: Social attraction in Drosophila is regulated by the mushroom body and serotonergic system
description: Robust social attraction in fruit flies relies on two prominent senses, vision and olfaction, which converge to central brain neurons. The neurons of the γ lobe of the mushroom bodies integrate sensory information and modulate social affinity.
